data.title: Game Sack 2021
data.text:
Notes:

*After the "Every Sega CD game in North America" episode, I wanted to do on that was quick and easy. This turned out to be anything but. The Mystical Ninja Goemon Zero segment turned out to be more than I thought it would be. Then later Saturn prototypes of Prize Fighter and Sacred Pools were found, so I decided to include those. A couple of weeks after that, Victor Ireland informed me of the Far East of Eden Ziria video he had and sent it to me. I ended up removing a SNES game that I can't even remember the name of. It was the shortest, least interesting, and weakest segment in the video, barely even being an alpha.
